3. Combining data

a) Macro-level data

Let us add the country-level data. There are two sources: macrodata_1.xlsx and macrodata_2.csv. Import the XLSX using the read_excel() function of the readxl package and assign it to an object macrodata_1. Import the CSV and assign it to macrodata_2. Which countries are included in the ESS but not in macrodata_1 and not in macrodata_2, respectively?

b) Preparing country-level data

Mcrodata_1 includes the following information:

  • GDP (gross domestic product) at current market prices - Purchasing Power Standards per inhabitant in percentage of the EU average 2016
  • Gini coefficient of equalized disposable income 2016

Mcrodata_1 includes:

  • Social expenditure in percentage of GNI (gross national income) 2015

How are these variables called in the data? Which variable will be the key variable for data merging? Make sure the key variable has the same name in all data sets (note that R is case sensitive).

c) Joining data

Combine the ESS with both macro-level data sets using one of the join functions from the dplyr package.
